<subSubSection id="C581654CFFC6CD3486E5FB9DFD2DFABB" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8D2436C7FFC6CD3486E5FB9DFD2DFABB" blockId="1.[151,1436,994,1484]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC6CD3486E5FB9DFE88FB93" bold="true" box="[197,317,1110,1136]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This species is distinct from any other one from the Apennines by frontal impressions of head relatively deep, basal impressions of pronotum foveate (not linear), elytral striae irregularly but finely punctate, each elytron usually with 
<number id="3B5324E0FFC6CD34846EFB6FFDE8FB5D" box="[590,605,1188,1214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="4.0">4</number>
dorsal SP and situation of second dorsal SP in middle of interval 
<number id="3B5324E0FFC6CD3483ADFB6FFA29FB5D" box="[1421,1436,1188,1214]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
(equidistantly from striae 
<number id="3B5324E0FFC6CD3487EBFB01FE6FFB07" box="[459,474,1226,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
and 
<number id="3B5324E0FFC6CD348435FB01FD90FB07" box="[533,549,1226,1252]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="3.0">3</number>
), medial lobe of aedeagus laterally curved, with twin-peaked apex sharply bent downwards and lobes twisted ventrally (
<figureCitation id="15A02A42FFC6CD348492FB3AFCB1FAE8" box="[690,772,1265,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 - 6" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1245,1269]" captionTargetBox="[174,1404,191,1244]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,157,1276]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 - 6. Median lobe of aedeagus left lateral view and parameres of Italian Platyderus: Fig. 1. Platyderus casalei sp. n., holotype; Fig. 2. P. magrinii Degiovanni, “ Mte Graeco ”; Fig. 3. P. neapolitanus Chaudoir, “ Emery Napels ”; Fig. 4. P. paganettii sp. n., holotype; Fig. 5. P. vignai sp. n., holotype; Fig. 6. P. vignai sp. n., holotype, parameres." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190889/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
Figs. 
<number id="3B5324E0FFC6CD3484D5FB3AFCB1FAE8" box="[757,772,1265,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="1.7">1</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="15A02A42FFC6CD348533FB3AFC91FAE8" box="[787,804,1265,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 - 10" captionStartId="3.[151,276,1325,1349]" captionTargetBox="[186,1406,599,1276]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,569,1316]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 - 10. Median lobe of aedeagus right lateral view and copulatory piece of Italian Platyderus: Fig. 7. Platyderus casalei sp. n., holotype; Fig. 8. P. paganettii sp. n., holotype; Fig. 9. P. vignai sp. n., holotype; Fig. 10. P. paganettii sp. n., holotype, dorsal and ventral shape of copulatory piece." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190890/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="15A02A42FFC6CD348512FB3AFCE5FAE8" box="[818,848,1265,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 - 18" captionStartId="6.[151,270,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[204,1415,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,194,1847]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11 - 18. Median lobe of aedeagus, ventral and dorsal views of Italian Platyderus: Fig. 11. Platyderus casalei sp. n., holotype, ventral view; Fig. 12. P. magrinii Degiovanni, “ Mte Graeco ”, ventral view; Fig. 13. P. neapolitanus Chaudoir, “ Emery Napels ”, ventral view; Fig. 14. P. paganettii sp. n., holotype, ventral view; Fig. 15. P. vignai sp. n., holotype, ventral view; Fig. 16. Platyderus casalei sp. n., holotype, dorsal view; Fig. 17. P. neapolitanus Chaudoir, “ Emery Napels ”, dorsal view; Fig. 18. P. vignai sp. n., holotype, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190891/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<number id="3B5324E0FFC6CD348512FB3AFCE5FAE8" box="[818,848,1265,1291]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
), copulatory piece with prominent medial lobe in front (
<figureCitation id="15A02A42FFC6CD3486C0FAD3FE83FAD1" box="[224,310,1304,1330]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 - 18" captionStartId="6.[151,270,1871,1895]" captionTargetBox="[204,1415,214,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,194,1847]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11 - 18. Median lobe of aedeagus, ventral and dorsal views of Italian Platyderus: Fig. 11. Platyderus casalei sp. n., holotype, ventral view; Fig. 12. P. magrinii Degiovanni, “ Mte Graeco ”, ventral view; Fig. 13. P. neapolitanus Chaudoir, “ Emery Napels ”, ventral view; Fig. 14. P. paganettii sp. n., holotype, ventral view; Fig. 15. P. vignai sp. n., holotype, ventral view; Fig. 16. Platyderus casalei sp. n., holotype, dorsal view; Fig. 17. P. neapolitanus Chaudoir, “ Emery Napels ”, dorsal view; Fig. 18. P. vignai sp. n., holotype, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190891/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number id="3B5324E0FFC6CD348737FAD3FE83FAD1" box="[279,310,1304,1330]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="4A9B4D44FFC6CD3487FBFAD3FDF9FAD2" box="[475,588,1304,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="casalei" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC6CD3487FBFAD3FE5FFAD2" box="[475,490,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC6CD3487D9FAD3FDF9FAD2" box="[505,588,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">casalei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC6CD348474FADCFD23FAD2" bold="true" box="[596,662,1303,1329]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A4DC57AEFFC6CD348474FADCFD23FAD2" box="[596,662,1303,1329]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="4A9B4D44FFC6CD348577FAD3FC59FAD2" box="[855,1004,1304,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paganettii" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC6CD348577FAD3FCD3FAD2" box="[855,870,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC6CD348555FAD3FC59FAD2" box="[885,1004,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">paganettii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC6CD3485D4FADCFB83FAD2" bold="true" box="[1012,1078,1303,1329]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A4DC57AEFFC6CD3485D4FADCFB83FAD2" box="[1012,1078,1303,1329]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the non-overlapping values of the ratios PW/HW, PW/PL, and EW/PW.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C581654CFFC6CD3686E5FAAEFCCFFEC5" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph id="8D2436C7FFC6CD3486E5FAAEFDBEFA2F" blockId="1.[151,1436,994,1484]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC6CD3486E5FAAEFEE2FA9C" bold="true" box="[197,343,1381,1407]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Description</emphasis>
. A micropterous 
<taxonomicName id="4A9B4D44FFC6CD348408FAAEFD1DFA9D" box="[552,680,1381,1406]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC6CD348408FAAEFD1DFA9D" box="[552,680,1381,1406]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Platyderus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, with microsculpture of tegument isodiametric, distinct on labrum, vertex and elytra. Colour dark brown, antennomeres, palpomeres and legs paler. Values for sizes and ratios are shown in Table 
<number id="3B5324E0FFC6CD3487D6FA79FDB3FA2F" box="[502,518,1458,1484]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" value="1.0">1</number>
.
</paragraph>
