<paragraph id="8D2436C7FFC4CD3686E5FF75FCCFFEC5" blockId="3.[151,1437,152,526]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
Chaetotaxy: interval 
<number id="3B5324E0FFC4CD36879AFF75FE7CFF3B" box="[442,457,190,216]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" value="3.0">3</number>
of each elytron with 
<number id="3B5324E0FFC4CD3684E2FF75FD64FF3B" box="[706,721,190,216]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" value="4.0">4</number>
SP (first SP situated in stria 
<number id="3B5324E0FFC4CD368201FF75FB85FF3B" box="[1057,1072,190,216]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" value="3.0">3</number>
at first third of elytron, second SP laying in middle of interval 
<number id="3B5324E0FFC4CD36843BFF2EFD99FF1C" box="[539,556,229,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" value="3.0">3</number>
, at middle of elytron, and last two SP situated in stria 
<number id="3B5324E0FFC4CD3682EDFF2EFB6AFF1C" box="[1229,1247,229,255]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
, in last third of elytron (third SP situated closer to forth SP than to second SP).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C581654CFFC4CD3686E5FEF9FE43FDED" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8D2436C7FFC4CD3686E5FEF9FD6DFE90" blockId="3.[151,1437,152,526]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC4CD3686E5FEF9FEFEFEAF" bold="true" box="[197,331,306,332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Etymology</emphasis>
. Dedicated to Prof. Dr. Achille Casale for his important contributions to the systematics and taxonomy of the Italian and European 
<taxonomicName id="4A9B4D44FFC4CD368479FE92FD61FE90" box="[601,724,345,371]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Carabidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D2436C7FFC4CD3686E5FEB4FE43FDED" blockId="3.[151,1437,152,526]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC4CD3686E5FEB4FEBEFE7A" bold="true" box="[197,267,383,409]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Notes</emphasis>
. The significant differences in the external structure of the male genitalia between 
<taxonomicName id="4A9B4D44FFC4CD3682C0FE4BFAE4FE7A" box="[1248,1361,384,410]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="casalei" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC4CD3682C0FE4BFB5BFE7A" box="[1248,1262,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC4CD3682DEFE4BFAE4FE7A" box="[1278,1361,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">casalei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC4CD368379FEB4FA29FE7A" bold="true" box="[1369,1436,383,409]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A4DC57AEFFC4CD368379FEB4FA29FE7A" box="[1369,1436,383,409]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4A9B4D44FFC4CD3686E8FE6CFEE8FE23" box="[200,349,422,448]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Platyderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paganettii" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC4CD3686E8FE6CFF62FE23" box="[200,215,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC4CD3686C6FE6CFEE8FE23" box="[230,349,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">paganettii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="BFEFEAD5FFC4CD368744FE6DFE13FE23" bold="true" box="[356,422,422,448]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A4DC57AEFFC4CD368744FE6DFE13FE23" box="[356,422,422,448]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, as well the state of several external special features (foveae of head; basal impression of pronotum) and non-overlapping ratios (PW/HW, PW/PL, EW/PW) could be the effect of rapid sympatric isolation of these related taxa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
